redits, since it paysa great rate of interest and safeguards against a hostile takeover. It's defcomis set at 9 which should discourage the other alliances from mounting an armedraid on it (we also patrol it when signing out of the game). The funds in theRebel Bank are for emergency use by the members, and it's hoped that eachwithdrawal can be replaced if possible by the withdrawee. The important thingfor the individual is to try and build his ship up, especially in the weaponand shields department, again, generally by scavenging derelict pirate ships.Alliances:It is a good idea to early on join one of the four alliances. Fellow allies canprovide help in dealing with the complexities of the game as well as discountedlaunch fees when launching from an ally's port. You can participate in thealliance banking systems as well as be privy to the alliance's bulletin board.Fellow allies will avoid attacking you when the circumstances for confrontationoccur. Banking:There are 3 types of banks present in Spacer Quest. The first is your alliance bank, where there is no interest, but everyone inyour alliance can deposit and withdraw credits. This is a mutual trustarrangement. It also allows for an alliance to transfer credits from one spacerto another. Can also act as an emergency fund for an alliance member introuble. The second is your alliance holding, which is a star system, which youralliance must first acquire, then defend. This account is mutually open to allthe members of your alliance as regards withdrawals, deposits, fortifying,etc.. This account draws daily interest. It is vulnerable to 'hostile takeover'by another alliance if the account is over 99,999 credits and vulnerable toarmed takeover by a 'corporate raider' from another alliance at anytime.Fortifying this holding can be done by increasing the DEFCOM from 1-9 at 100Kper level and will defend the holding against enemy space ships bent on raidingyour holding.The third is if you own a space port and receive launch fees from others usingyour port. You can use this account as a personal bank for your own depositsand withdrawals. There is no interest given here. Brig (Jail):The Brig is located on Sun-3. Commonest crime for being incarcerated is beingcaught by the space patrol for smuggling. Most serious crime to be convicted ofis losing carrier (disconnecting your modem while on-line) during battle(sometimes thought of as an easy way to avoid being destroyed by superioropponents). Juris P. Magnus, Esq, Provost Marshal of The Space Patrol presidesover the legal affairs. Prisoners can either pay their fines and be released orhave a fellow spacer pay bail (costs double the fine) for them. Goals in Spacer Quest:Individuals win by attaining 10,001 or more total points, at which time theywill be written into The Great Book for their outstanding achievement. Theythen may have the option of starting the game over.Alliances win by attaining control of the majority of the local 14 star systemholdings. This will be determined by the sysop who will then declare thealliance holding majority to be the winner. At this point the sysop may thendecide to reset the game.Disclaimer of responsibility:The sysops who so generously manage this bbs and have installed this on-linegame for your enjoyment do not take any responsibility for any emotionaltrauma, peptic ulcers, hypertension, or other claimed physical or emotionalinjuries suffered as a result of playing Spacer Quest. It has been said thatthis game is alot like life itself......'no one said that life had to be fair'Remember, this is a game intended to be played for fun by all. It is also avery highly user-interactive game with many open-ended options allowed to theplayer. Opportunities for complex strategies can evolve during the course ofthe game, as well.-------------------------------------------------------------------------------